Aug 18 2009 	Pleasant surprise	Stayed for almost a week with partner in this downtown hotel while doing research, attending a conference, and doing some sightseeing. Cost and location were big influences in making the reservation. We expected something &quot;decent,&quot; but for the most part it was a pleasant surprise.The staff were incredibly helpful at check-in and throughout the stay, giving tips about the surrounding area including where to park for cheap (the hotel does have some limited parking of its own but there is a fee). Our hotel room was on the top floor, facing the next-door residential building so not exactly a room with a view (unless you're a voyeur) but the windows were screened and a nice breeze came through with them open. There was some noise from people living in the other building (and perhaps other hotel rooms with open windows) but not disturbingly loud - we had no problems sleeping.The building/rooms are old but partially remodeled - nice carpet and tile, LOTS of closet space, spacious bathroom, kitchenette area with microwave and minifridge. Quaint murals throughout the hotel, including in the rooms (rooms are named based on landmarks in the city, with a matching mural in the room). We had a &quot;deluxe queen&quot; room which was quite spacious with a small seating area, desk, and TV armoire. The rooms are not AC climate controlled (not unusual in SF) but with the fan and open windows we were quite comfortable (and there was a warm spell while there).Neither of us were impressed with the continental breakfast - mostly carbs and nothing mouthwatering.We had problems with the wireless internet not being available the first morning but after speaking with the front desk it was fixed and no further problems during the trip.The hotel is convenient to most of the downtown area and many public transportation options. It is a bit of a hike to the fisherman's wharf area but we did walk it one day and it was pleasant (though we rode back on the trolley). The front desk did point out to us when we checked in that the tenderloin area is somewhat nearby and what areas to avoid - we had no problems.	
